					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="2v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
							<note>
								<p>Consists of a number of fragments: Genesis 1:1-49:7, Exodus 5:14-17:6, Deuteronomy 22:3-25:9, Leviticus 4:20-7:27, 13:37-17:12, 9:22-13:37, Numbers 4:11-6:2, Leviticus 27:7-Numbers 1:49, Numbers 14:36-19:13, Deuteronomy 18:22-22:3, 29:24-34:12. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 16th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>31 membranes, 116 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>556 (825mm with the rollers)</height>
										<width>1992</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>31 membranes, with wooden rollers. Silk, brocade and linen mantle. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Ink offset to verso. </p>
									<p>Damaged roller. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="116" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="42">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stiching. </p>
									<p>116 columns in total, three to five columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהיק. </p>
									<p>Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah, with a few exceptions. </p>
								
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
